    • Constructor Detail

      • InferenceForFactorGraphAndEvidence

        public InferenceForFactorGraphAndEvidence(FactorsAndTypes factorsAndTypes,
                                          boolean isBayesianNetwork,
                                          Expression evidence,
                                          boolean useFactorization,
                                          Theory optionalTheory)
        Constructs a solver for a factor graph and an evidence expression.
        Parameters:
        factorsAndTypes - the factors and their type information over which inference is to be performed.
        isBayesianNetwork - indicates if the factor graph is a bayesian network (each potential function in normalized for one of its variables, forms a DAG).
        evidence - an Expression representing the evidence
        useFactorization - indicates whether to use factorization (as in Variable Elimination)
        optionalTheory - the theory to be used; if null, a default one is used (as of May 2017, a compound theory with propositional, equalities on categorical types, difference arithmetic, and real linear arithmetic).
